modules.name: AWS.MediaStoreData
modules.comments: An AWS Elemental MediaStore asset is an object, similar to an object in the Amazon S3 service. Objects are the fundamental entities that are stored in AWS Elemental MediaStore.

declarations.comments: Deletes an object at the specified path.
declarations.title: deleteObject

declarations.comments: Gets the headers for an object at the specified path.
declarations.title: describeObject

declarations.comments: Downloads the object at the specified path.
declarations.title: getObject

declarations.comments: Provides a list of metadata entries about folders and objects in the specified folder.
declarations.title: listItems

declarations.comments: Uploads an object to the specified path. Object sizes are limited to 10 MB.
declarations.title: putObject

declarations.comments: The specified container was not found for the specified account.
declarations.title: ContainerNotFoundException

declarations.comments: A metadata entry for a folder or object.
declarations.title: Item

declarations.comments: Could not perform an operation on an object that does not exist.
declarations.title: ObjectNotFoundException

declarations.comments: The requested content range is not valid.
declarations.title: RequestedRangeNotSatisfiableException
